In the lower stratosphere, the maximum cooling signal is at high latitudes in the Southern Hemisphere (SH), where ozone depletion has been largest (
 Fig. 3
  A
 ). Cooling is smaller but significant in the tropics. The between-realization variability of TLS trends is largest over both poles and smallest in the deep tropics (
 Fig. 3
  D
 ). These signal and noise patterns explain why TLS S/N ratios reach maximum values in the tropics (
 Fig. 3
  G
 ).
